element.name: Memories By The Water by RoswellJam, Virtual Cache (1/1)
element.description: A short walk from the city centre with nice views.
element.long-description:
Down by the water you'll see what life was like in the past and what it is still like for millions of people around the world. You will see names of some of Ireland's famous people and remember those who you will never know.
E-mail me with the answer to the following question to claim a find.
On what exact date did the Canadian Prime Minister visit here?

2010-06-14T19:00:00Z : Found it by Hemel Staggers
I would probably have strolled past here without paying much attention to this memorial. So thanks for making me stop and think. TFTC

2010-06-09T19:00:00Z : Found it by Just Roger
Saw these sculptures last night while driving through Dublin from the ferry in the middle of rush hour. Also saw that there was a ghost icon there on Tomtom so came back while visiting Dublin today to do the cache. Interesting place. E-mail sent with answer to question

2010-06-01T19:00:00Z : Found it by eve1987
Poor people and a very interesting location.
TFTC and kind regards from Austria, eve

2010-06-01T19:00:00Z : Found it by GudrunXY
A quick find with eve1987 on our caching tour through Ireland. TFTC GudrunXY

Thank you for the cache Team CrazyGustav & Ruth

2005-10-01T07:00:00Z : Found it by Kersti.com
What a moving monument. The statues looked so emotive - brilliant work. Found the date, and my looking for the info seemed to interest some others. Pretty soon there were muggles everywhere!
